title: I’m A Celebrity Australia 2017: Bachelor contestant Keira joins show
text:
Share on Twitter 
DESCRIBING herself as “exactly what the camp needs,” Bachelor alum Keira Maguire is headed to the South African jungle as the I’m A Celebrity, Get Me Out Of Here intruder in tonight’s epiosde. 
Labelled as the Bachelor season four ‘villain’, Maguire lasted eight episodes in the show until after Bachelor Richie refused her a rose. Bachelor Richie Strahan refused to give Keira a rose. Source: Channel 10 
Since appearing on The Bachelor , 30-year old Keira has made no secret of the fact she’d like to be on reality television programs. 
And, tonight she’s going to get exactly what she wanted, heading to the jungle to join the 12 other celebrities already in camp. 
“We’ll see how people respond to my outspoken ways,” she said in a Twitter video. ANNOUNCING: @oshergunsberg has a special gift for our celebs. @TheBachelorAU ’s KEIRA is ready to shake up the #ImACelebrityAU camp. pic.twitter.com/YNNks2qVeO — #ImACelebrityAU (@ImACelebrityAU) February 11, 2017 
Keira, who famously clashed with a number of Bachelor contestants, also admitted she doesn’t think she’s going to get on with everyone. 
“I’m probably going to clash with Ash,” she said. “As a watcher I think I’d like her but going in, I think we’ll have different opinions.” 
Despite worrying she’ll clash with the My Kitchen Rules alum, there is one person she thinks she’ll find some common ground with. 
“I have a little bit of a hunch that I’ll get along with Kris Smith,” she said. 
“I don’t know what it is. Could be the biceps, could be the rig,” she added. 
If you’re worried Keira isn’t going to bring the drama like she did on The Bachelor, the reality star revealed she won’t disappoint. 
“I’m super excited about getting in the jungle because I can’t wait to get under their skin,” she said. 
“Ha ha just joking, not really,” she added. 
I’m A Celebrity, Get Me Out Of Here airs tonight at 7pm on Network Ten.
